pageTitle: Vietnam Tour of Duty Photographs of Dennis Mannion
pageIntro:
A collection of photographs of PFC Dennis J. Mannion (Delta Company, 1st Battalion, 3rd Marines) taken near and during his tour of duty in the Vietnam War. Most of these photos are assumed to have been taken at Camp Schwab in Okinawa. Dennis died on May 5, 1967 in an ambush on Delta Company during Operation Beaver Cage. His name is on panel 19E, line 43 of The Wall.

Photographs published with family permission as compliments to The Cage, an in-progress book project.
